. Inappropriate laboratory test over requesting is extremely frequent. The prevalence of under requesting has been less studied. The consequences of under requesting are clear, we are missing a diagnosis. Inappropriate over requesting can result not only in a problem of cost but also in a problem regarding patient safety. Additionally, another important consequence of inappropriate tests over requesting is that such amount of unnecessary tests has probably contributed to a significant increase in the volume of those over the last years. In all, there is general consensus that the inadequacy of test requesting must be corrected through strategies and monitored over time through indicators to assure the optimal laboratory contribution to clinical decision-making and patient safety.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aDiagnosis, Laboratory. 0aMedical carexQuality control. 0aMedical errors. 0aMedical laboratoriesxSafety measures. 4aAngemessenheit. 4aClinical Laboratory. 4aKlinisches Labor. 4aPatient safety. 4aPatientensicherheit. 4aTestanforderung. 4aappropriateness test request. 4aclinical outcomes. 7aMEDICAL / Microbiology.2bisacsh1 aBlasco, Álvaro, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBlasco, Álvaro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarratalá, Arturo, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aCarratalá, Arturo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLopez-Garrígos, Maite, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLópez-Garrigós, Maite, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRodriguez-Borja, Enrique, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRodriguez-Borja, Enrique, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relat